page_title: 'Customize a model with Azure OpenAI Service and the Python SDK'
page_description: Learn how to create your own customized model with Azure OpenAI Service by using the Python SDK.
chunk_content: Prerequisites- Read the When to use Azure OpenAI fine-tuning guide.- An Azure subscription. Create one for free.- An Azure OpenAI resource. For more information, see Create a resource and deploy a model with Azure OpenAI.- The following Python libraries: `os`, `json`, `requests`, `openai`.- The OpenAI Python library should be at least version 0.28.1.- Fine-tuning access requires Cognitive Services OpenAI Contributor.- If you do not already have access to view quota, and deploy models in Azure OpenAI Studio you will require additional permissions.
